          "title": "cmake: Add hardening, reduce exports, werror, libbitcoinconsensus and install",
          "body": "New CMake variables that affect the build system configuration:\r\n- `HARDENING`\r\n- `REDUCE_EXPORTS`\r\n- `WERROR`\r\n- `BUILD_SHARED`\r\n- `BUILD_STATIC`\r\n- `BUILD_BITCOINCONSENSUS_LIB`\r\n\r\nThe suggested implementation allows to build both static and shared `libbitcoinconsensus` libraries simultaneously (as Autotools do). However, in the https://github.com/bitcoin-core/secp256k1 repository, the different [approach](https://github.com/bitcoin-core/secp256k1/pull/1230) was adopted.\r\n\r\nSo I'm open to suggestions regarding the best approach.",
